<item>
            <title>[SPR-5149] Use MessageFormat to pass messages to spring Assert</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-5149</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using Spring Assert class to check preconditions, the message is expected to be a String. If you want to pass contextual datas in the message, this requires some String concat even if condition is validated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to follow slf4j example and support a MessageFormat pattern. With help of varargs, we could write :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Assert.isTrue( text.length() &amp;lt;= maxSize, &quot;Value &apos;&lt;/p&gt;
{0}
&lt;p&gt;&apos; is too large ! max size is &lt;/p&gt;
{1}
&lt;p&gt;&quot;, text, maxSize );&lt;/p&gt;</description>
